Thank you!

1257
01:25:32,740 --> 01:25:33,740
Thank you, truly!

1258
01:25:36,400 --> 01:25:37,520
Thank you!

1259
01:25:40,560 --> 01:25:41,840
And we also want to thank

1260
01:25:41,840 --> 01:25:45,560
the public security, culture, fire and other departments

1261
01:25:45,560 --> 01:25:46,660
for their strong support.

1262
01:25:46,660 --> 01:25:48,180
Thanks as well to our venue,

1263
01:25:48,180 --> 01:25:50,080
the Chengdu High-Tech Sports Center.

1264
01:25:50,080 --> 01:25:52,080
And thanks to all our Chengdu hometown friends.

1265
01:25:52,080 --> 01:25:54,800
Thank you!

1266
01:25:56,960 --> 01:25:58,560
Now let's wipe away our tears

1267
01:25:58,560 --> 01:26:00,360
and welcome the next stage,

1268
01:26:00,360 --> 01:26:00,680
okay?

1269
01:26:00,680 --> 01:26:01,560
Okay.

1270
01:26:01,560 --> 01:26:03,360
We'll hand the stage back to Lusi.

1271
01:26:03,360 --> 01:26:04,080
Please.

1272
01:26:09,260 --> 01:26:12,820
["Hidden Heart" lyrics: Er Shui, music: Chen Zhuni]

1273
01:29:56,860 --> 01:29:58,580
A round of applause for Lusi!

1274
01:30:01,660 --> 01:30:03,620
Tonight's performances have been amazing.

1275
01:30:04,100 --> 01:30:05,580
No matter the style,

1276
01:30:05,580 --> 01:30:07,340
Lusi's voice can bring it

1277
01:30:07,820 --> 01:30:09,620
to everyone through music.

1278
01:30:10,220 --> 01:30:11,100
So, what's next?

1279
01:30:11,820 --> 01:30:14,460
Now it's time for some interaction.

1280
01:30:14,460 --> 01:30:15,740
In this segment,

1281
01:30:15,740 --> 01:30:17,940
we're going to quiz

1282
01:30:18,500 --> 01:30:20,340
everyone here.

1283
01:30:20,340 --> 01:30:21,980
We'll pick a few people

1284
01:30:21,980 --> 01:30:23,420
who are willing to answer

1285
01:30:23,420 --> 01:30:24,780
these nine questions in my hand.

1286
01:30:24,780 --> 01:30:26,740
Our staff

1287
01:30:26,740 --> 01:30:27,980
will bring the mic

1288
01:30:27,980 --> 01:30:29,180
right over to you.

1289
01:30:29,180 --> 01:30:31,380
You can use this chance

1290
01:30:31,380 --> 01:30:32,780
to answer the question

1291
01:30:32,780 --> 01:30:34,380
and say what you'd like to say to Lusi.

1292
01:30:34,380 --> 01:30:34,860
How does that sound?

1293
01:30:35,980 --> 01:30:36,460
All right.

1294
01:30:36,460 --> 01:30:38,020
We'll start on this side.

1295
01:30:38,020 --> 01:30:39,500
I know you're super enthusiastic here.

1296
01:30:40,340 --> 01:30:42,380
Who wants to answer a question?

1297
01:30:45,700 --> 01:30:47,340
If you get it wrong, you'll have to leave right away.

1298
01:30:47,340 --> 01:30:48,140
Kidding.

1299
01:30:48,140 --> 01:30:48,780
Nothing like that.

1300
01:30:49,980 --> 01:30:50,540
Let me see.

1301
01:30:51,340 --> 01:30:52,580
Our staff has reached you,

1302
01:30:52,580 --> 01:30:52,980
right?

1303
01:30:52,980 --> 01:30:53,420
Okay, they're there.

1304
01:30:53,420 --> 01:30:55,180
All right, let me see

1305
01:30:55,180 --> 01:30:57,180
who's feeling confident enough to try.

1306
01:30:58,380 --> 01:30:59,100
Let's go with her!

1307
01:30:59,100 --> 01:31:00,260
The one holding the fan sign.

1308
01:31:00,260 --> 01:31:01,100
Yeah.

1309
01:31:01,100 --> 01:31:01,780
In the purple top,

1310
01:31:01,780 --> 01:31:02,500
same color as mine.

1311
01:31:02,500 --> 01:31:03,500
Yes, you!

1312
01:31:05,060 --> 01:31:06,620
Pass her the mic.

1313
01:31:09,140 --> 01:31:10,980
Take a breath first.

1314
01:31:10,980 --> 01:31:11,860
Introduce yourself.

1315
01:31:13,580 --> 01:31:14,580
What should we call you?

1316
01:31:14,580 --> 01:31:15,900
Hello, everyone.

1317
01:31:15,900 --> 01:31:17,420
I'm Xiaoxuan.

1318
01:31:17,420 --> 01:31:17,900
Xiaoxuan,

1319
01:31:18,140 --> 01:31:19,540
could you share your seat number

1320
01:31:20,100 --> 01:31:21,620
so our staff can note it down?

1321
01:31:21,940 --> 01:31:24,540
Section 205, Row 3, Seat 1.

1322
01:31:24,540 --> 01:31:25,180
All right.

1323
01:31:25,180 --> 01:31:25,940
Got it.

1324
01:31:25,940 --> 01:31:26,780
Okay, Xiaoxuan,

1325
01:31:27,460 --> 01:31:28,780
pick a number first.

1326
01:31:28,780 --> 01:31:30,220
From one to nine.

1327
01:31:31,220 --> 01:31:31,620
Six.

1328
01:31:32,780 --> 01:31:33,460
So decisive.

1329
01:31:33,460 --> 01:31:34,100
Okay, let's see.

1330
01:31:34,660 --> 01:31:36,380
Xiaoxuan's question is...

1331
01:31:36,380 --> 01:31:37,220
Xiaoxuan,

1332
01:31:38,180 --> 01:31:40,140
how many points did you get in the Canelé quiz?

1333
01:31:42,820 --> 01:31:43,420
When grabbing tickets,

1334
01:31:43,420 --> 01:31:44,700
what was your score on the test?

1335
01:31:44,700 --> 01:31:45,020
Do you remember?

1336
01:31:45,020 --> 01:31:46,700
It didn't show the score.

1337
01:31:46,700 --> 01:31:48,140
So you passed straight away, right?

1338
01:31:48,140 --> 01:31:48,820
All right then.

1339
01:31:48,820 --> 01:31:50,980
Let's open envelope number six.

1340
01:31:52,380 --> 01:31:53,020
Here we go.

1341
01:31:53,020 --> 01:31:54,260
"Prove you're a fan of Zhao Lusi

1342
01:31:54,260 --> 01:31:56,060
in one sentence,

1343
01:31:56,060 --> 01:31:57,340
but you can't use

1344
01:31:57,340 --> 01:31:59,260
'sweet' or 'cute' in it."

1345
01:31:59,740 --> 01:32:00,740
Just one sentence.

1346
01:32:00,740 --> 01:32:01,420
You can take a moment

1347
01:32:01,900 --> 01:32:02,700
to think how you'll prove it.

1348
01:32:06,300 --> 01:32:07,660
All eyes are on you.

1349
01:32:08,580 --> 01:32:09,460
You've got this, Xiaoxuan.

1350
01:32:10,380 --> 01:32:11,140
Don't worry, just kidding.

1351
01:32:11,700 --> 01:32:12,220
Relax.

1352
01:32:13,900 --> 01:32:15,700
Here she goes. Xiaoxuan looks ready.

1353
01:32:18,060 --> 01:32:18,940
Every person

1354
01:32:19,460 --> 01:32:20,500
is special.

1355
01:32:24,580 --> 01:32:26,020
Every girl

1356
01:32:26,020 --> 01:32:27,140
is the most special of all.

1357
01:32:27,140 --> 01:32:29,020
"Special" is what matters most.

1358
01:32:32,860 --> 01:32:35,780
Can I say something to Lusi too?

1359
01:32:35,780 --> 01:32:36,580
Of course.

1360
01:32:36,580 --> 01:32:37,780
Will she hear me?

1361
01:32:37,780 --> 01:32:38,460
Of course.

1362
01:32:38,460 --> 01:32:39,860
She's wearing in-ears right now.

1363
01:32:39,860 --> 01:32:40,580
She can hear everything.

1364
01:32:41,700 --> 01:32:43,060
Can I say something from the heart?

1365
01:32:44,460 --> 01:32:46,020
I'm a fan

1366
01:32:46,020 --> 01:32:49,100
who's loved Lusi for eight years.

1367
01:32:49,100 --> 01:32:50,860
Ever since the very beginning, with Luo Feifei,

1368
01:32:50,860 --> 01:32:52,220
I've liked you all the way.

1369
01:32:52,820 --> 01:32:55,340
This journey hasn't been easy for any of us,

1370
01:32:55,340 --> 01:32:56,860
but I can clearly see

1371
01:32:56,860 --> 01:32:58,740
every effort you make,

1372
01:32:58,740 --> 01:33:01,900
how you pour in your heart on every stage

1373
01:33:01,900 --> 01:33:03,100
and in every drama,

1374
01:33:03,100 --> 01:33:04,260
and how you improve.

1375
01:33:04,260 --> 01:33:05,580
We see it all.

1376
01:33:05,980 --> 01:33:06,940
Zhao Lusi,

1377
01:33:06,940 --> 01:33:08,140
you're truly amazing!

1378
01:33:09,300 --> 01:33:10,780
Every single one of us Canelés

1379
01:33:10,780 --> 01:33:12,300
will always believe in you,

1380
01:33:12,300 --> 01:33:13,780
support you and stay by your side,

1381
01:33:14,260 --> 01:33:14,820
forever.

1382
01:33:15,820 --> 01:33:16,420
Zhao Lusi,

1383
01:33:16,420 --> 01:33:17,740
you can charge ahead bravely.

1384
01:33:18,820 --> 01:33:20,140
Your Canelés will always be there.

1385
01:33:21,620 --> 01:33:22,260
Thank you!

1386
01:33:22,260 --> 01:33:24,180
Thank you, Xiaoxuan, for speaking

1387
01:33:24,940 --> 01:33:26,020
everyone's heart.

1388
01:33:26,020 --> 01:33:27,140
Xiaoxuan, you're just as special.

1389
01:33:27,140 --> 01:33:28,140
You're our very first one tonight.

1390
01:33:28,140 --> 01:33:28,900
Wonderful!

1391
01:33:28,900 --> 01:33:30,820
We'll keep your seat number on record.

1392
01:33:30,820 --> 01:33:31,860
I'll tell you later

1393
01:33:31,860 --> 01:33:32,860
what you'll receive.

1394
01:33:32,860 --> 01:33:33,540
All right,

1395
01:33:33,940 --> 01:33:35,060
let's move over here!

1396
01:33:35,900 --> 01:33:37,580
Who wants to answer a question?

1397
01:33:39,900 --> 01:33:40,380
Let me see.

1398
01:33:42,940 --> 01:33:45,300
Who?

1399
01:33:46,100 --> 01:33:46,860
How about her?

1400
01:33:46,860 --> 01:33:48,380
The one holding the hand banner.

1401
01:33:49,540 --> 01:33:51,020
The one with the big banner.

1402
01:33:51,620 --> 01:33:51,940
Okay,

1403
01:33:51,940 --> 01:33:53,020
the one in white.

1404
01:33:53,660 --> 01:33:53,900
Come on.

1405
01:33:54,460 --> 01:33:55,660
Please introduce yourself.

1406
01:33:55,660 --> 01:33:59,980
I'm Jov, from Singapore.

1407
01:33:59,980 --> 01:34:00,940
Welcome!

1408
01:34:00,940 --> 01:34:01,820
Thanks for coming such a long way.

1409
01:34:02,380 --> 01:34:03,220
Welcome.

1410
01:34:03,220 --> 01:34:08,020
Our whole row here are overseas Lusi fans.

1411
01:34:08,020 --> 01:34:09,060
Welcome!

1412
01:34:09,980 --> 01:34:11,220
Welcome to all of you!

1413
01:34:11,220 --> 01:34:12,460
Which number will you pick?

1414
01:34:13,100 --> 01:34:13,620
Nine.

1415
01:34:13,620 --> 01:34:14,300
Okay.

1416
01:34:14,300 --> 01:34:14,780
Your question is:

1417
01:34:14,780 --> 01:34:16,780
If Lusi appeared right next to you,

1418
01:34:16,780 --> 01:34:19,620
what little thing would you most want to do with her?

1419
01:34:20,060 --> 01:34:21,180
Can I give her a hug?

1420
01:34:24,100 --> 01:34:25,500
So just a hug is enough, right?

1421
01:34:25,500 --> 01:34:26,220
A hug full of love, right?

1422
01:34:26,220 --> 01:34:27,460
Why do you want to hug Lusi?

1423
01:34:29,700 --> 01:34:30,980
Because...

1424
01:34:30,980 --> 01:34:32,780
because I love her.

1425
01:34:32,780 --> 01:34:34,540
Love means hugging,

1426
01:34:34,540 --> 01:34:35,820
and love means meeting often.

1427
01:34:35,820 --> 01:34:37,260
Thanks all for coming from so far away.

1428
01:34:37,260 --> 01:34:39,260
Could I ask for your seat number?

1429
01:34:39,900 --> 01:34:40,900
It's...

1430
01:34:40,900 --> 01:34:44,340
Section 218, Row 1, Seat 16.

1431
01:34:44,340 --> 01:34:44,820
All right.

1432
01:34:44,820 --> 01:34:46,380
Director, please note that down.

1433
01:34:46,380 --> 01:34:47,620
In a bit we'll...

1434
01:34:47,620 --> 01:34:50,860
Can I speak on their behalf too?

1435
01:34:50,860 --> 01:34:51,420
You can.

1436
01:34:51,420 --> 01:34:53,020
Here, we also have fans

1437
01:34:53,020 --> 01:34:54,460
from Thailand,

1438
01:34:54,460 --> 01:34:55,460
Korea,

1439
01:34:55,460 --> 01:34:57,180
Russia,

1440
01:34:58,260 --> 01:34:59,580
Malaysia...

1441
01:35:01,900 --> 01:35:03,700
fans from many countries.

1442
01:35:03,700 --> 01:35:07,660
There are a lot of overseas Lusi fans.

1443
01:35:07,660 --> 01:35:10,740
This time, it's all thanks to the fans

1444
01:35:10,740 --> 01:35:11,620
back in China too.

1445
01:35:12,460 --> 01:35:14,220
They helped us a lot.

1446
01:35:14,220 --> 01:35:15,100
What a kind of bond.

1447
01:35:15,100 --> 01:35:16,180
Yes.

1448
01:35:16,180 --> 01:35:18,140
Because Lusi once said

1449
01:35:18,140 --> 01:35:20,540
"love can give everyone strength,"

1450
01:35:20,540 --> 01:35:21,820
we also hope

1451
01:35:21,820 --> 01:35:24,260
our love from overseas and from home

1452
01:35:24,260 --> 01:35:25,980
can give her strength.

1453
01:35:25,980 --> 01:35:26,540
Thank you!

1454
01:35:27,020 --> 01:35:27,580
Thank you!

1455
01:35:28,380 --> 01:35:30,140
I hope Canelés all over the world

1456
01:35:30,140 --> 01:35:32,020
can all become good friends

1457
01:35:32,020 --> 01:35:34,260
and have lots of chances to come to Chengdu.

1458
01:35:34,260 --> 01:35:34,620
Okay?

1459
01:35:34,620 --> 01:35:35,300
Welcome, all of you!

1460
01:35:35,300 --> 01:35:36,620
Stay tuned for what's next.

1461
01:35:36,620 --> 01:35:38,380
As for the two of you just now,

1462
01:35:38,380 --> 01:35:40,860
our friend over here

1463
01:35:40,860 --> 01:35:41,540
and Xiaoxuan there,

1464
01:35:41,540 --> 01:35:43,260
after the show,

1465
01:35:43,260 --> 01:35:44,180
our staff will do their best

1466
01:35:44,180 --> 01:35:45,260
to contact you

1467
01:35:45,260 --> 01:35:46,740
and put a small token of our thanks

1468
01:35:46,740 --> 01:35:47,820
right into your hands.

1469
01:35:47,820 --> 01:35:48,580
Thank all of you

1470
01:35:48,580 --> 01:35:51,180
for supporting tonight's concert,

1471
01:35:51,180 --> 01:35:52,980
especially everyone who's traveled so far.

1472
01:35:52,980 --> 01:35:53,820
Next up,

1473
01:35:54,260 --> 01:35:56,500
let's all get ready together

1474
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:58,740
for our last big party tonight!

1475
01:35:58,740 --> 01:35:59,540
Are you ready?

1476
01:36:00,340 --> 01:36:01,780
We're ready!

1477
01:36:01,780 --> 01:36:03,260
Please welcome Zhao Lusi!

1478
01:36:04,300 --> 01:36:06,300
[Don't Wanna Know]

1479
01:36:06,300 --> 01:36:08,460
[Lyrics & music: Brian Lee, vocal coach: Mischke]

1480
01:37:26,500 --> 01:37:27,460
Come on!

1481
01:39:35,980 --> 01:39:36,940
Thank you!

1482
01:39:52,020 --> 01:39:54,420
Wow, here comes an angel!

1483
01:40:02,540 --> 01:40:04,900
[2025.11.04, Band Rehearsal Day]

1484
01:40:06,660 --> 01:40:08,380
We start from here, right?

1485
01:40:08,380 --> 01:40:08,940
Okay.

1486
01:40:08,940 --> 01:40:10,620
Can you catch the beat?

1487
01:40:10,620 --> 01:40:11,500
I can.

1488
01:40:11,500 --> 01:40:13,420
I can't catch if from you two,

1489
01:40:13,420 --> 01:40:15,140
but I can just follow the keyboard.

1490
01:40:29,940 --> 01:40:31,820
Your cue coming in is spot on

1491
01:40:31,820 --> 01:40:32,980
Because I was really focused.

1492
01:40:32,980 --> 01:40:35,500
I locked in on this one thing.

1493
01:40:55,220 --> 01:40:56,860
Want to run through this song again?

1494
01:40:56,860 --> 01:40:57,420
Yeah.

1495
01:40:57,420 --> 01:40:58,060
Okay.

1496
01:41:12,540 --> 01:41:17,060
[2025.11.05, Choreography Day]

1497
01:41:25,900 --> 01:41:29,220
I'm worried I'll get nervous and grab their hair.

1498
01:41:44,060 --> 01:41:47,620
Both rap bits are just the dance, so it feels off..

1499
01:41:47,620 --> 01:41:50,500
So if your lip-sync can match

1500
01:41:50,500 --> 01:41:52,140
the Sichuan line too...

1501
01:41:52,140 --> 01:41:54,340
Wow!

1502
01:42:17,780 --> 01:42:19,020
You're all in pairs,

1503
01:42:19,020 --> 01:42:21,260
and I'm the only one here alone.

1504
01:42:21,820 --> 01:42:26,660
[2025.11.06, Stage Rehearsal Day]

1505
01:42:34,740 --> 01:42:36,220
Right, this is where you do this.

1506
01:42:36,220 --> 01:42:37,780
Yes.

1507
01:43:00,740 --> 01:43:03,780
Let's do that again. Okay.

1508
01:43:27,260 --> 01:43:30,660
[2025.11.08, The Promised Day]

1509
01:43:31,860 --> 01:43:33,620
["Only One"]
You knew I'd come back, right?

1510
01:43:33,620 --> 01:43:35,100
[Lyrics & music: Pan Yun'an; Adaptation: G.E.M.]

1511
01:45:03,420 --> 01:45:05,020
You all know this one, right?

1512
01:47:15,220 --> 01:47:16,980
There are so much words,

1513
01:47:19,940 --> 01:47:21,540
a whole year's worth of words,

1514
01:47:21,540 --> 01:47:24,180
that I can't possibly finish tonight

1515
01:47:25,500 --> 01:47:27,780
But I've realized I really cry a lot.

1516
01:47:28,900 --> 01:47:30,060
Ever since

1517
01:47:31,140 --> 01:47:32,620
that big breakdown,

1518
01:47:33,780 --> 01:47:35,260
I can no longer hold in

1519
01:47:35,260 --> 01:47:36,460
any little emotion.

1520
01:47:40,820 --> 01:47:42,300
But for this last song,

1521
01:47:42,300 --> 01:47:44,500
why did I choose "Only One"?

1522
01:47:46,660 --> 01:47:48,780
Because this past year,

1523
01:47:48,780 --> 01:47:50,620
I really haven't been able

1524
01:47:50,820 --> 01:47:52,980
to listen to it alone at home.

1525
01:47:54,420 --> 01:47:57,260
But every time after an event,

1526
01:47:57,260 --> 01:47:59,300
I see you all singing it yourselves.

1527
01:48:01,180 --> 01:48:03,220
So today,

1528
01:48:04,500 --> 01:48:06,980
I want to sing it together with you.

1529
01:48:08,420 --> 01:48:09,980
And after that, I won't fear

1530
01:48:09,980 --> 01:48:11,460
this song anymore.

1531
01:48:11,940 --> 01:48:12,820
Okay?

1532
01:48:12,820 --> 01:48:14,700
Okay!

1533
01:48:15,020 --> 01:48:15,900
Are you ready?

1534
01:49:18,980 --> 01:49:23,860
Bye bye!

1535
01:49:54,420 --> 01:49:55,500
It's so hard

1536
01:49:55,500 --> 01:49:56,980
to say goodbye to you.

1537
01:49:56,980 --> 01:49:58,500
But I believe

1538
01:49:58,500 --> 01:49:59,860
brief partings

1539
01:49:59,860 --> 01:50:01,500
are for better reunions.

1540
01:50:02,060 --> 01:50:03,220
Once again thank you

1541
01:50:03,220 --> 01:50:05,620
to every passionate Canelés here

1542
01:50:05,620 --> 01:50:06,180
with us tonight.

1543
01:50:06,180 --> 01:50:06,980
Thanks for your

1544
01:50:07,220 --> 01:50:08,020
cheers,

1545
01:50:08,380 --> 01:50:09,300
screams,

1546
01:50:09,700 --> 01:50:10,260
singing,

1547
01:50:10,340 --> 01:50:11,340
your hand dances

1548
01:50:11,340 --> 01:50:12,380
and all your warmth.

1549
01:50:12,580 --> 01:50:14,500
I'm sure Lusi will hold it all in her heart

1550
01:50:14,700 --> 01:50:16,420
as the strength to keep going.

1551
01:50:16,980 --> 01:50:17,860
Tonight,

1552
01:50:17,860 --> 01:50:19,860
our concert is called "Miss You".

1553
01:50:20,380 --> 01:50:21,380
If I had to add one more line

1554
01:50:21,380 --> 01:50:22,980
to that name, it would be

1555
01:50:23,460 --> 01:50:24,660
"like the first dew".

1556
01:50:25,100 --> 01:50:26,300
"Missing you,

1557
01:50:26,460 --> 01:50:27,900
like the first dew".

1558
01:50:27,980 --> 01:50:29,020
I hope that every time we meet,

1559
01:50:29,020 --> 01:50:30,100
it can be like

1560
01:50:30,140 --> 01:50:31,780
the dew at daybreak,

1561
01:50:32,100 --> 01:50:32,820
clear,

1562
01:50:33,340 --> 01:50:34,260
pure,

1563
01:50:34,460 --> 01:50:36,740
and full of the sweetness of our very first meeting.

1564
01:50:37,180 --> 01:50:38,580
One more round of applause for yourselves

1565
01:50:38,580 --> 01:50:40,060
and for the one we all love most,

1566
01:50:40,380 --> 01:50:43,980
Zhao Lusi!

1567
01:50:43,980 --> 01:50:45,660
Blessings to Lusi and to all of you!

1568
01:50:45,660 --> 01:50:47,380
I hope your lives are filled with joy!

1569
01:50:47,380 --> 01:50:48,540
And may every day

1570
01:50:48,540 --> 01:50:49,740
shine bright!

1571
01:50:49,740 --> 01:50:50,980
See you soon.

1572
01:50:50,980 --> 01:50:51,820
Good night!

1573
01:50:52,580 --> 01:50:53,940
Thank you to everyone on this side!

1574
01:50:55,660 --> 01:50:57,020
You've all worked so hard!
